UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'It is important to be aware that all information is not created equal, and sources of information should be assessed with care and scrutiny.  This is particularly true in today’s digital age, where information is readily available and often presented without context or qualification. The following passage discusses the importance of evaluating sources of information: \"There are several factors to consider when evaluating a source of information, and one of the most important is the source’s credibility.  A credible source is one that is reliable, accurate, and unbiased.  For example, a news article from a well-respected news organization is more likely to be credible than a blog post by an anonymous author.  Other important factors include the source’s purpose and the date of publication.  It is important to understand the purpose of a source, such as to inform, to persuade, or to entertain.  It is also important to consider whether the information is up-to-date, as information can become outdated quickly."',
